(Kyber + AES-256 together \(why both\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Key point: Kyber does not replace AES for payload encryption. They serve different roles.) Tj
T*
(- AES-256-GCM role:) Tj
T*
(- Encrypt the actual wallet secret payload \(private key parts + mnemonic data\).) Tj
T*
(- Provide confidentiality + integrity tag over the payload.) Tj
T*
(- Kyber role:) Tj
T*
(- Wrap/encapsulate the DEK used by AES payload encryption.) Tj
T*
(- Provide a post-quantum recovery/unlock control plane for key material.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Practical model:) Tj
T*
(- Generate random DEK.) Tj
T*
(- Encrypt wallet secret payload with AES-256-GCM\(DEK\).) Tj
T*
(- Wrap DEK with password-derived KEK \(Argon2id + AES-256-GCM wrap\).) Tj
T*
(- Also wrap the same DEK with Kyber KEM metadata/ciphertext.) Tj
T*
(- Store encrypted payload + both wrap records in lockbox metadata.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This gives:) Tj
T*
(- fast encryption performance \(AES\),) Tj
T*
(- password UX for daily use,) Tj
T*
(- PQC-capable DEK recovery path \(Kyber\),) Tj
T*
(- and policy flexibility to tighten one plane without rewriting payload format.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(How keys are used) Tj
T*
(- Wallet CLI: signs transactions with the selected key; displays Base56 addresses derived from) Tj
T*
(HPK.) Tj
T*
(- Miner: uses the configured key for coinbase rewards and block signing.) Tj
T*
(- API: keys are separate \(see Src/Config/Api_Keys.json\), but the key manager feeds addresses for) Tj
T*
(wallet/miner actions.) Tj
T*
(- Wallet management API \(added\): POST /wallet/rename, POST /wallet/delete, POST /wallet/default) Tj
T*
(let the GUI rename, delete, or set a default key \(one default per network\). They resolve) Tj
T*
(identifiers by id/base56/HPK and refuse to delete the last key in a network.) Tj
T*
(- Wallet lockbox API \(added\):) Tj
T*
(- GET /wallet/unlock_status) Tj
T*
(- POST /wallet/unlock) Tj
T*
(- POST /wallet/lock) Tj
T*
(- POST /wallet/change_password) Tj
T*
(- POST /wallet/export_kyber_unlock_file) Tj
T*
(- POST /wallet/export_encrypted_backup) Tj
T*
(- POST /wallet/import_encrypted_backup) Tj
T*
(- GET /wallet/lock_policy) Tj
T*
(- POST /wallet/lock_policy) Tj
T*
(- sensitive wallet operations \(create/recover/import/export/sign/send/rename/delete/default\) now) Tj
T*
(fail closed with wallet_locked when encrypted and locked.) Tj
T*
(- unlock endpoint includes brute-force controls \(per-client backoff + temporary lockout after) Tj
T*
(repeated failures\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Safety notes) Tj
T*
(- The JSON file can run unencrypted \(legacy\) or encrypted lockbox mode.) Tj
T*
(- In lockbox mode, private/public raw key material and mnemonic data are encrypted and) Tj
T*
(unavailable until unlock.) Tj
T*
(- Mnemonic passphrases are never stored in key JSON or export files; keep passphrases) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
