(separately.) Tj
T*
(- Wallet encryption passwords now require non-empty input \(no fixed minimum length enforced by) Tj
T*
(backend\).) Tj
T*
(- Wallet exports are .txt and are marked read-only on save.) Tj
T*
(- Each node/container should have its own Keys directory; don?t share across independent nodes) Tj
T*
(unless you intend to reuse the same addresses.) Tj
T*
(- For production, add OS-level permissions \(e.g., chmod 600 Keys/*.json\) and consider an) Tj
T*
(encrypted keystore if you extend the system. A simple AES-GCM+scrypt proof-of-concept CLI exists) Tj
T*
(at Src/Accounts/ecript.py for manual encryption/decryption tests.) Tj
T*
(- Key file writes are lock-protected \(<key_file>.lock\) to reduce concurrent-write corruption) Tj
T*
(risk.) Tj
T*
(- Saves use backup-on-write and keep rolling backups in Keys/backups/ before replacing the) Tj
T*
(active key JSON.) Tj
T*
(- During plaintext -> encrypted migration, KeyManager no longer creates a new plaintext) Tj
T*
(pre_write backup and now purges any existing plaintext-secret backups under Keys/backups/.) Tj
T*
(- Mnemonic sidecar files \(Keys/mnemonic_recovery/...\) are automatically removed once wallet) Tj
T*
(lockbox encryption is enabled.) Tj
T*
(- Startup/disk reload now applies strict schema validation and fails closed on malformed key) Tj
T*
(files instead of silently proceeding with bad structure.) Tj
T*
(- Wallet backup/import paths for encrypted snapshots are validated under the keys root and use) Tj
T*
(the same atomic/backup controls.) Tj
T*
(- Unlock auto-relock policy:) Tj
T*
(- default unlock window is 30 seconds \(_wallet_policy.unlock_ttl_seconds\),) Tj
T*
(- 0 disables auto-relock timer,) Tj
T*
(- lock status includes unlock_expires_in_seconds.) Tj
T*
(- API unlock session state now persists across calls while key-file fingerprint is unchanged) Tj
T*
(\(prevents accidental relock-on-every-request\).) Tj
T*
(- wallet_unlock_status no longer exposes absolute key-file paths by default.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Addresses and HPK) Tj
T*
(- Public keys are hashed \(SHA3-384\) ? HPK ? encoded to Base56 for display.) Tj
T*
(- Base56 avoids ambiguous characters and is used consistently across CLI and wallet displays.) Tj
T*
(- Transaction witness wire format uses canonical base64 for pubkey/signature; KeyManager still) Tj
T*
(operates on internal hex/bytes for Falcon signing and verification.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Defaults and generation) Tj
T*
(- At load, the manager ensures at least miner_1 and miner_2 exist on mainnet, testnet, and) Tj
T*
(regnet; defaults are set to miner_1 if missing.) Tj
T*
(- Canonical miner slots are miner_1 and miner_2; additional miner identifiers \(miner_3+\) are) Tj
T*
(still supported and preserved.) Tj
T*
(- Only CLI-format keys are kept. Legacy/non-CLI records are regenerated as CLI keys.) Tj
T*
(- New key generation defaults to mnemonic-backed derivation with 24 words unless explicitly) Tj
T*
(overridden.) Tj
T*
(- CLI key-creation/import/recovery flow now prompts \(interactive TTY only\) to enable encryption) Tj
T*
(before proceeding when wallet is still unencrypted.) Tj
T*
(- Changing the default key updates all roles for that network and is enforced by the API and) Tj
T*
(GUI.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Recovery audit trail) Tj
T*
(- Mnemonic recovery operations are written to:) Tj
T*
(- logs/.../wallet/wallet_recovery_audit.log) Tj
T*
(- Audit records include timestamp, network, identifier, canonical source, and canonical flag so) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
