T*
(supported; legacy warning-header export format is still accepted for backward compatibility\).) Tj
T*
(- CLI helper \(change_default_key.py import\): still accepts JSON with fields public_key, f, g, F,) Tj
T*
(G, optional hpk/address_base56 \(HPK/Base56 are recomputed when present\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Import safeguards:) Tj
T*
(- Rejects/ignores duplicates by HPK or Base56; identifier collisions are auto-renamed \(import_1,) Tj
T*
(import_2, ?\) when HPK/Base56 are unique.) Tj
T*
(- Recomputes HPK and ensures provided HPK/Base56 matches.) Tj
T*
(- Runs a test sign before persisting.) Tj
T*
(- Requires at least one key per network; deletion is blocked only if it would remove the last) Tj
T*
(key.) Tj
T*
(- GUI export enforces read-only .txt; imports are no longer hard-coupled to one literal) Tj
T*
(warning-header line.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Exporting keys \(wallet\) for offline storage) Tj
T*
(- From the wallet tab, use the export/download icon to save a single key to a .txt file. The) Tj
T*
(file:) Tj
T*
(- Is forced to .txt and marked read-only on save.) Tj
T*
(- Contains private/public key material, HPK/Base56, and mnemonic phrase/word list sections when) Tj
T*
(the key is mnemonic-derived.) Tj
T*
